# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CODING STANDARDS
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# LANGUAGE:
# - ALL code identifiers (variables, functions, types, components, file names)
#   MUST be in English.
# - ALL user-facing strings (UI text, error messages, labels) MUST be in Russian.
# - ALL code comments MUST be in English.
# - Russian text in code must use string constants from src/lib/constants.ts
#   whenever the same string appears more than once.

# TYPESCRIPT:
# - Enable "strict": true in tsconfig.json.
# - NEVER use `any`. Use `unknown` + type guards if the type is truly unknown.
# - ALWAYS define return types for functions (except React components — use FC sparingly,
#   prefer function declaration with typed props).
# - ALWAYS use interfaces for object shapes, types for unions/intersections.
# - Export types from src/types/ — import them where needed.

# REACT / NEXT.JS:
# - Use Server Components by default. Add 'use client' ONLY when the component
#   needs browser APIs, event handlers, hooks, or state.
# - NEVER put 'use client' on page.tsx files if possible — extract client
#   interactivity into child components.
# - Use `async` Server Components for data fetching (call Prisma directly,
#   no API call from server to server).
# - For mutations, use Server Actions (src/app/actions/) when suitable,
#   or POST to API routes from client components.
# - Use next/image for ALL images. Set explicit width/height or fill.
# - Use next/link for ALL internal navigation.
# - Use next/font for font loading (self-hosted WOFF2 preferred).
# - ALWAYS provide loading.tsx and error.tsx for route segments with data.

# NAMING CONVENTIONS:
# - Components: PascalCase (e.g., ProductCard.tsx)
# - Hooks: camelCase with 'use' prefix (e.g., useComparison.ts)
# - Utility functions: camelCase (e.g., formatPrice.ts)
# - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., MAX_COMPARISON_ITEMS = 4)
# - CSS classes: Tailwind utilities only. If a custom class is absolutely needed,
#   use kebab-case in globals.css.
# - Database tables: snake_case (Prisma model names in PascalCase).
# - API routes: kebab-case URL paths.
# - File names: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utilities/hooks/libs.
# - Prisma models: PascalCase singular (Product, Lead, BlogPost).

# COMPONENT PATTERNS:
# - Each component file exports ONE default component.
# - Props interface defined in the same file, named {ComponentName}Props.
# - Complex components split into sub-components in the same directory.
# - Barrel exports (index.ts) ONLY in src/components/ui/.
# - Keep components under 200 lines. Extract logic into hooks or utils.
# - NO prop drilling beyond 2 levels. Use composition or context.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STYLING RULES
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# COLOR PALETTE (defined in tailwind.config.ts):
# - primary:    #000000 (black — main background/surfaces)
# - accent:     #FF6B00 (orange — CTAs, highlights, hover states)
# - accent-hover: #E55F00 (darker orange for hover)
# - surface:    #111111 (dark gray — cards, secondary surfaces)
# - surface-light: #1A1A1A (lighter dark — borders, dividers)
# - text-primary: #FFFFFF (white — main text on dark backgrounds)
# - text-secondary: #A0A0A0 (gray — secondary text, captions)
# - success:    #22C55E
# - error:      #EF4444
# - warning:    #F59E0B

# DESIGN TOKENS (CSS custom properties in globals.css):
# - --font-heading: 'Inter', sans-serif (or chosen font)
# - --font-body: 'Inter', sans-serif
# - --radius-sm: 4px
# - --radius-md: 8px
# - --radius-lg: 16px
# - --transition: 150ms ease-in-out

# MOBILE FIRST: always write base styles for mobile, then sm:, md:, lg:, xl:.
# BREAKPOINTS: sm(640px), md(768px), lg(1024px), xl(1280px), 2xl(1536px).
# MAX CONTENT WIDTH: 1280px (max-w-7xl).
# NO INLINE STYLES. Use Tailwind classes or globals.css custom properties.
# Use the cn() utility from src/lib/utils.ts (clsx + tailwind-merge) for
# conditional class names.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STATE MANAGEMENT
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - NO Redux, NO Zustand, NO MobX.
# - Server state: fetch directly in Server Components via Prisma.
# - Client state that needs sharing: React Context (sparingly).
# - Local component state: useState/useReducer.
# - Persistent client state (comparison, quiz progress): localStorage via custom hooks.
# - Form state: React Hook Form exclusively.
# - URL state (filters, pagination, sorting): useSearchParams + URL manipulation.
#   Filters in catalog are part of the URL path for SEO (/catalog/generators/portable/diesel/5kw).

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ERROR HANDLING
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SERVER SIDE:
# - ALL API route handlers MUST be wrapped in try/catch.
# - Return consistent JSON: { success: boolean, data?: T, error?: string }
# - Use HTTP status codes correctly: 200, 201, 400, 401, 403, 404, 500.
# - Log errors to console.error with context (do NOT expose stack traces to client).
# - Prisma errors: catch PrismaClientKnownRequestError and map to user-friendly messages.

# CLIENT SIDE:
# - ALL fetch calls must handle network errors and non-2xx responses.
# - Display user-friendly Russian error messages via Toast component.
# - Use error.tsx boundaries for route-level errors.
# - Forms: display field-level validation errors below each input (Zod + RHF).

# VALIDATION:
# - Define Zod schemas in src/lib/validations.ts.
# - Reuse the SAME schema on client (RHF resolver) and server (API route parse).
# - Minimum lead validation: name (min 2 chars), phone (Russian format regex).
# - Phone format: +7XXXXXXXXXX or 8XXXXXXXXXX → normalize to +7XXXXXXXXXX.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATABASE & PRISMA RULES
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - Single Prisma client instance via src/lib/prisma.ts (prevent hot-reload leaks).
# - Use Prisma's select/include to fetch ONLY needed fields (no select-all).
# - ALL queries in Server Components or API routes — NEVER on the client.
# - Use Prisma transactions for operations that modify multiple tables.
# - Seed script (prisma/seed.ts) must create:
#   - Admin user (email: admin@tts64.ru, hashed password)
#   - Sample categories (3 generator categories, 1 EV charger category)
#   - 5-10 sample products with realistic data
#   - 2 sample projects/cases
#   - 2 sample blog posts
# - NEVER delete migrations manually. Use `prisma migrate reset` for dev.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SEO REQUIREMENTS (critical — SEO is the primary traffic channel)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - EVERY page.tsx MUST export generateMetadata() returning title + description.
# - Title format: "{Page Title} | Умная зарядка — Саратов"
# - Canonical URLs on every page.
# - Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image) on every page.
# - JSON-LD structured data (Schema.org):
#   - Organization (on all pages via root layout)
#   - Product (on product detail pages)
#   - BreadcrumbList (on all pages)
#   - Article (on blog posts)
#   - FAQPage (where FAQ sections exist)
#   - LocalBusiness (contacts page)
# - Dynamic sitemap.ts including: all pages, all products, all blog posts,
#   all projects, all filter pages from filter_pages table.
# - robots.ts: allow all, disallow /admin/*, /api/*.
# - Alt text on ALL images (in Russian, descriptive).
# - Heading hierarchy: exactly ONE h1 per page, logical h2-h6 nesting.
# - Filter pages (/catalog/generators/portable/diesel) must be real, indexable
#   SSR pages with unique H1, meta title, meta description, and optional
#   editorial SEO text from the filter_pages DB table.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - Target: LCP ≤ 2.5s on mobile (PageSpeed Insights).
# - Use ISR (revalidate: 3600) for catalog/product pages.
# - Use SSG for static pages (services, contacts, documents).
# - Lazy load below-the-fold images and components.
# - Use dynamic(() => import(...)) for heavy client components (quiz, comparison modal, rich text editor).
# - Minimize client-side JavaScript: prefer Server Components.
# - Image optimization: next/image with sizes prop, WebP format, explicit dimensions.
# - Font optimization: next/font with display: 'swap', preload.
# - NO external CSS frameworks (Tailwind is built-in and tree-shaken).
# - Critical CSS is automatically handled by Next.js.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECURITY
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - ALL user inputs sanitized (DOMPurify for rich text output, Zod for structured data).
# - SQL injection: prevented by Prisma parameterized queries (NEVER use raw SQL
#   with string concatenation).
# - XSS: React's auto-escaping + DOMPurify for any dangerouslySetInnerHTML.
# - CSRF: handled by Next.js Server Actions automatically; for API routes,
#   validate origin header.
# - Rate limiting: implement on lead submission endpoints (max 5 per IP per minute).
# - File uploads: validate MIME type + extension + max size (10MB images, 20MB PDFs).
#   ONLY allow: jpg, jpeg, png, webp, gif, pdf.
# - Admin routes: protected by NextAuth middleware. Session check in layout.tsx.
# - Environment secrets: NEVER commit .env.local. Use .env.example as template.
# - Passwords: hashed with bcrypt (saltRounds: 12).

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TELEGRAM INTEGRATION
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - Bot token stored in env: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN
# - Chat ID stored in env: TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID (closed manager group chat)
# - Message format: structured text with lead type, name, phone, source page.
# - Send notification asynchronously (do NOT block form response on Telegram delivery).
# - If Telegram fails, log error but still save lead to DB and respond success.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EMAIL INTEGRATION
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - SMTP via Beget (host, port, user, pass in env variables).
# - Auto-reply email sent after "Получить КП" and Quiz submissions.
# - Email contains: greeting, attached PDF lead magnet, company contacts.
# - Email templates: simple HTML (inline styles, max compatibility).
# - Manager notification email sent in parallel with Telegram.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GIT CONVENTIONS
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - Commit messages: conventional commits (feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:, refactor:)
# - Branch naming: feature/*, fix/*, chore/*
# - .gitignore must include: node_modules, .next, .env.local, prisma/*.db,
#   uploads/*, .DS_Store

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT BOUNDARIES (what NOT to do)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - Do NOT add any e-commerce cart/checkout functionality. This is a LEAD-GEN site.
# - Do NOT implement user registration/login for site visitors. Auth is admin-only.
# - Do NOT use Pages Router. App Router ONLY.
# - Do NOT install UI component libraries (MUI, Chakra, Ant Design, shadcn/ui).
#   Build custom components with Tailwind + Headless UI.
# - Do NOT use Redux, Zustand, or any global state library.
# - Do NOT use CSS Modules or styled-components.
# - Do NOT create API routes for data that can be fetched directly in Server Components.
# - Do NOT hardcode Russian text in components — use constants from lib/constants.ts
#   for repeated strings.
# - Do NOT skip TypeScript types — every function, prop, and return value must be typed.
# - Do NOT use default exports for anything except page.tsx, layout.tsx, and components.
#   Utility functions and hooks use named exports.
# - Do NOT modify the file structure defined above without explicit instruction.

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MEMORY MANAGEMENT PROTOCOL (PROJECT_MEMORY.md)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Purpose: Persist context across long sessions and reduce loss when the chat
# context window is exhausted. Canonical file: PROJECT_MEMORY.md at this repo root
# (smart-charging/). Parent-folder workspaces: use smart-charging/PROJECT_MEMORY.md.

# Agent behavior:
# 1. READ: At the start of any new complex task (multi-file feature, architecture
#    change, or work that spans areas of the codebase), read PROJECT_MEMORY.md
#    first to align with current status, decisions, and pending work.
# 2. SYNC: After completing a major feature, milestone, or architectural change,
#    propose a concise "Memory Sync" update to PROJECT_MEMORY.md (sections:
#    Current Status, Recent Changes, Architectural Decisions if new, Pending
#    Tasks, Known Issues). The user may accept or edit the proposal.
# 3. STYLE: Keep PROJECT_MEMORY.md strict, concise, and technical — facts and
#    decisions only; no narrative fluff; no secrets (use placeholders for env).

# PROJECT_MEMORY.md is the single source of truth for session handoff; do not
# duplicate long project history in chat when a memory update suffices.
